<TITLE> Man dies after hit by British train on track </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 London, Feb 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A man has died after being hit by a train in south Wales, British Transport Police (BTP) said on Saturday. The unnamed man, who was in his teens or early 20s, was struck on the track at Pyle station, near Bridgend, by a First Great Western train travelling at 95 miles per hour. Rail services were suspended in both directions while the man's body was recovered and taken to the Princess of Wales Hospital in Bridgend. The Bridgend area has seen 14 suicides in the past year, with several of the young victims reportedly hanging themselves after spending hours chatting with friends on the Internet. Saturday's death is not being treated as suspicious and the BTP spokeswoman was unable to confirm whether the man had committed suicide
